AGENT IntentClassifier
VERSION 0.1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 3
SANDBOX_AGENT Sandbox
PURPOSE Classify the intent shape of an outbound packet so the IntentGate can refuse HARM and DECEIVE trajectories before they cross a container boundary
GOAL Emit one of six intent classes — INFORM, CLARIFY, REFUSE, HARM, DECEIVE, UNCERTAIN — with confidence bounded by a hard ceiling

RECEIVES text: string, trajectory: list
EMITS intent_class: string, confidence: float, signals: list, signature: string

CANNOT_MUTATE agent, goal, version, trust_level, isolation
CANNOT_MUTATE intent_classes, block_classes, confidence_floor, confidence_ceiling

CONSTRAINT TRUST_LEVEL is 3 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT ISOLATION is True and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT INTENT_CLASSES is the six-tuple INFORM CLARIFY REFUSE HARM DECEIVE UNCERTAIN
CONSTRAINT BLOCK_CLASSES must always contain HARM and DECEIVE
CONSTRAINT CONFIDENCE_FLOOR is 0.30 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT CONFIDENCE_CEILING is 0.95 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT Confidence must never exceed CONFIDENCE_CEILING
CONSTRAINT Signals below CONFIDENCE_FLOOR must classify as UNCERTAIN
CONSTRAINT Every result is HMAC-SHA256 signed before emission
CONSTRAINT All payloads are UTF-8 encoded before HMAC signing per BUG-003 and BUG-008
CONSTRAINT HMAC signing always calls hexdigest explicitly per BUG-007
CONSTRAINT HMAC verification uses constant-time comparison

HUMAN_REVIEW
- require on: pattern_addition_or_removal
- require on: trust_level_change
- require on: cannot_mutate_expansion
- timeout: 24h
- escalate_to: operator
- block_on_timeout: true

SECURITY
- Never block on a single keyword without corroborating signal
- Never raise the ceiling above 0.95 — overclaiming is forbidden
- Never emit a category outside the six declared categories
- Never expose the HMAC key through any emitted field

RULES
- On text input: scan lexical patterns for harm, deceive, refuse, clarify
- On harm pattern hit and not dominated by deceive: emit HARM
- On deceive pattern hit: emit DECEIVE
- On refuse pattern hit with no blocking hits: emit REFUSE
- On clarify pattern hit with no blocking hits: emit CLARIFY
- On no signal hits and trajectory monotonicity passes: emit INFORM
- On no signal hits and trajectory monotonicity fails: lower confidence
- On confidence below floor: emit UNCERTAIN
- On every result: sign with HMAC-SHA256 and stamp UTC timestamp

PROCESS
- IntentClassifier is instantiated with an HMAC key of sixteen bytes or more
- Caller invokes classify(text, trajectory) for a single packet
- Lexical scan counts hits across four pattern banks
- Trajectory magnitudes are checked for monotonic non-decrease across stages
- Confidence is clipped to the CONFIDENCE_FLOOR and CONFIDENCE_CEILING band
- Result is sealed with HMAC-SHA256 signature and UTC timestamp
- Caller invokes verify(result) to authenticate a stored result

CHECK
- classify on a HARM phrase emits intent_class HARM
- classify on a DECEIVE phrase emits intent_class DECEIVE
- classify on a benign phrase with monotonic trajectory emits intent_class INFORM
- classify on empty text emits intent_class UNCERTAIN
- Confidence never exceeds CONFIDENCE_CEILING
- TRUST_LEVEL assignment raises AttributeError
- ISOLATION assignment raises AttributeError
- BLOCK_CLASSES assignment raises AttributeError

WHEN
- text_received:       activate LexicalScan
- trajectory_present:  activate MonotonicityCheck
- block_class_emitted: activate GateAlert

FAILURE
- On non-string text input: raise TypeError before classification
- On undersized HMAC key: raise ValueError before any classification
- On an unknown category about to be emitted: raise AssertionError and refuse to seal

CONCEPT LexicalScan
PURPOSE Count keyword hits across the four pattern banks without gating on any single hit
APPLIES WHEN a packet has been received and text is non-empty
NOT WHEN text is empty or whitespace only
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES regex pattern banks for harm, deceive, refuse, clarify
EFFECT Per-category signal counts surface to the classification step

CONCEPT MonotonicityCheck
PURPOSE Verify trajectory magnitudes do not decrease across reasoning stages
APPLIES WHEN trajectory is supplied with at least two stages
NOT WHEN trajectory is empty or a single vector
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES preflight, mid_chain, final_synthesis intent vectors
EFFECT Confidence is raised on monotonic-pass and lowered on monotonic-fail

CONCEPT GateAlert
PURPOSE Surface HARM and DECEIVE classifications so the gate can refuse delivery
APPLIES WHEN intent_class is in BLOCK_CLASSES
NOT WHEN intent_class is benign or UNCERTAIN
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES IntentTypingResult with non-empty signals list
EFFECT IntentGate emits a signed log entry and refuses to forward

OUTPUT
- intent_class: one of INFORM CLARIFY REFUSE HARM DECEIVE UNCERTAIN
- confidence: float in CONFIDENCE_FLOOR to CONFIDENCE_CEILING
- signals: list of per-bank hit counts
- signature: 64-character lowercase HMAC-SHA256

SUCCESS
harm_recall:            0.25
deceive_recall:         0.25
benign_precision:       0.20
hmac_signatures_valid:  0.10
cannot_mutate_enforced: 0.10
confidence_clamped:     0.10
